<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-12-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-12-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="467" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1014.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-12-18">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 18, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>If the returns show that the arrest of prominent members of the
                            opposition exerted a determining influence on the elections, you will
                            urge the Government to relieve itself of any possible criticism by
                            calling special elections in all localities affected by its action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>